The paper deals with the formalization of inductive proofs in the string diagrams of compact closed and traced symmetric monoidal categories, which is a topic that falls under the area of logic (cs.LO). It also introduces an extension to string graphs to allow for the representation of certain infinite families of graphs and graph rewrite rules, which is related to computational complexity (cs.CC) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the use of string diagrams in quantum information theory, which falls under the area of programming languages (cs.PL) and quantum computing (cs.QA).
